System to be modelled:
Automatic Emergency Break of a car (AEB)
For this modelling, sensors like radar sensors, camera sensors, wheel speed sensors and braking pedal sensors will be used.
This system is used in modern cars to prevent or reduce the risk of accidents.
It is usually placed in the front bumper of cars.
This system plays a crucial role in nowadays road system.
PSEUDOCODE:
Get SpeedOfCar
If SpeedOfCar > 0
	Read data from forward facing sensor
	Read data from camera sensor
		If ObjectDetected = True
			calculate distanceFromObject 
			calculate relativeSpeed
				If PotentialRisk = True
					 If braking is applied = True
						no action
					else
						applyBraking
					end
				else
					no action
				end
		else
			no action
else 
	no action
end
